{
  "stem": "2170.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was-- she managed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was a very fine [NON-ENGLISH], that with not money, even she could manage.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Every time-- every month it came in from my father, the money, she paid for all the things for the house.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was really beautiful.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My sisters, my brothers, the older ones-- they had friends.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They belonged-- already, my older brother and sister-- to Zionist organizations.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And always in our house was a house of friends.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she was loved by everybody in my town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then, growing older and hoping that my father can bring us to America-- but he was not an American citizen at that time.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He became an American citizen in 1938.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And as soon as he became an American citizen, he sent affidavits to the American Embassy in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he wrote already at that time letters that a fire starts to burn in Europe.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he would like us to come out as soon as, with God's help, that he can bring us over to the United States.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But because-- the American Embassy in Warsaw was not so friendly towards Jewish emigration.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And was hard that he had to put up a lot of money to show that he can bring us over.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he had to borrow this.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he tried everything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "In end of 1938, in the beginning of 1939, we received already letters from American Embassy in Warsaw that he needed more affidavits.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he tried to do that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Before the war started in 1939, he thought that we will be over.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We'll come over.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And the American Embassy, only two weeks before the war started, notified my mother that there is a visa for all of us to go to the United States.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
